 Manchester United defeated Leeds United 6-2 in their Premier League match on Sunday at the Old Trafford. Scott McTominay scored twice in three minutes to open the floodgate before Bruno Fernandes and Victor Lindelof added to the tally in the first half. Raphinha Cooper reduced the lead to make it 4-1 in the opening 45 minute, in the second half Daniel James and Fernandes scored again to increase the lead it 6-1, Stuart Dallas was on target for the visitors to reduce the deficit to 6-2. Leeds United has conceded four first-half goals in a Premier League match for the first time, in what is their 482nd game in the competition. Scott McTominay became the first player in Premier League history to score twice in the first three minutes